United legends describe Liverpool loss as having "no heart, soul or leaders”and the global giant is set for a rebuild. A clearly unhappy Ralf Rangnick branded Manchester United's 4-0 thrashing by Liverpool at Anfield as “embarrassing and humiliating”. Jürgen Klopp's side pulled two points ahead in the Premier League title race before Manchester City host Brighton on Wednesday. Having lost 5-0 in the reverse at Old Trafford, United has lost the season head-to-head 9-0 on aggregate.